---
// About Page - explains Project Nirv and NIRV meaning
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/base-layout.astro";
import Header from "../components/header.astro";
import Footer from "../components/footer.astro";
import SectionLayout from "../components/section-layout.astro";
import ResearchCard from "../components/research-card.astro";

// Featured research for tiles
const featuredResearch = [
  {
    id: "adaptive-systems",
    title: "Adaptive Systems in Global Supply Chains",
    brief: "How non-linear feedback loops reshape resilience.",
    date: "2025-01-15",
    tag: "Systems",
  },
  {
    id: "market-dynamics",
    title: "Market Dynamics Under Uncertainty",
    brief: "Pricing mechanisms in distributed decision-making.",
    date: "2025-01-12",
    tag: "Markets",
  },
  {
    id: "emergence-patterns",
    title: "Emergence Patterns in Complex Systems",
    brief: "How order arises from chaos without coordination.",
    date: "2025-01-08",
    tag: "Ideas",
  },
  {
    id: "data-methodology",
    title: "Data Collection Methodology",
    brief: "Best practices for non-linear data sources.",
    date: "2025-01-05",
    tag: "Notes",
  },
];
---

<BaseLayout title="About">
  <Header />

  <main class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 py-12 md:py-16">
    <!-- Header -->
    <div class="mb-12">
      <h1 class="font-mono font-bold text-4xl text-white mb-4">About Project Nirv</h1>
      <p class="font-mono text-lg text-cyan-accent italic">
        A direction for structured research and non-linear insight.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Content -->
    <article class="space-y-12">
      <SectionLayout title="The Project">
        <p>
          Project Nirv is a structured research initiative dedicated to understanding complex systems through the
          lens of non-linear dynamics. We investigate how intelligence emerges from interconnected networks, how
          markets evolve under uncertainty, and how novel ideas germinate in the space between disciplines.
        </p>
        <p>
          Our work bridges theory and practice, combining rigorous data analysis with conceptual exploration. We
          believe that many of today's most pressing challenges cannot be solved with linear thinking—they require
          frameworks that embrace complexity, feedback loops, and emergent behavior.
        </p>
      </SectionLayout>

      <SectionLayout title="NIRV: Non-Linear Intelligence Research Vector">
        <p>The acronym NIRV encapsulates our research philosophy:</p>
        <p>
          <strong class="text-cyan-accent">Non-Linear:</strong> We reject reductionist models that assume simple
          cause-and-effect relationships. Real systems exhibit feedback loops, tipping points, and qualitative shifts.
        </p>
        <p>
          <strong class="text-cyan-accent">Intelligence:</strong> Intelligence—whether in markets, ecosystems, or
          organizations—is a collective phenomenon. We study how distributed agents generate emergent order and adaptation.
        </p>
        <p>
          <strong class="text-cyan-accent">Research:</strong> Systematic inquiry grounded in data, theory, and peer
          scrutiny. We privilege evidence over ideology and rigor over convention.
        </p>
        <p>
          <strong class="text-cyan-accent">Vector:</strong> A vector is both a direction and a magnitude. NIRV
          represents both the trajectory of our research and the force behind structured insight.
        </p>
      </SectionLayout>

      <SectionLayout title="Research Areas">
        <p>
          <strong class="text-white">Systems:</strong> Complex adaptive systems, network topology, emergence,
          and resilience in large-scale networks.
        </p>
        <p>
          <strong class="text-white">Markets:</strong> Market dynamics, pricing mechanisms, information
          asymmetry, and valuation frameworks under uncertainty.
        </p>
        <p>
          <strong class="text-white">Ideas:</strong> Conceptual frameworks, theoretical exploration, and
          cross-disciplinary synthesis.
        </p>
        <p>
          <strong class="text-white">Notes:</strong> Methodological observations, data practices, and research infrastructure.
        </p>
      </SectionLayout>

      <SectionLayout title="Philosophy">
        <p>We believe research should be:</p>
        <p>
          <strong class="text-white">Rigorous:</strong> Grounded in evidence, transparent in methodology, and
          open to critique.
        </p>
        <p>
          <strong class="text-white">Accessible:</strong> Written clearly for both specialists and informed
          generalists. Complexity of thought should not require obscurity of language.
        </p>
        <p>
          <strong class="text-white">Cumulative:</strong> Building on the work of others, acknowledging our
          intellectual debts, and contributing to a broader body of knowledge.
        </p>
        <p>
          <strong class="text-white">Exploratory:</strong> Willing to follow questions wherever they lead, even
          into uncertainty and ambiguity.
        </p>
      </SectionLayout>

      <!-- Featured Research Tiles -->
      <SectionLayout title="Featured Research">
        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mt-6">
          {featuredResearch.map((item) => (
            <ResearchCard
              id={item.id}
              title={item.title}
              brief={item.brief}
              date={item.date}
              tag={item.tag}
            />
          ))}
        </div>
      </SectionLayout>

      <SectionLayout title="Get In Touch">
        <p>
          We welcome collaboration, critique, and conversation. If you are interested in our research or wish to
          contribute, please reach out.
        </p>
        <p class="text-cyan-accent text-sm">inquiry@projectnirv.com</p>
      </SectionLayout>
    </article>
  </main>

  <Footer />
</BaseLayout>
